article.headline: Wright St. 68, Cleveland St. 55
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio (AP) -- Todd Brown scored 22 points to lead Wright State to a 68-55 win over Cleveland State Wednesday night. Raheem Moss made a jumper to pull the Vikings (8-19, 2-12 Horizon League) to a 51-51 tie with 9:14 to play. The Raiders (20-8, 13-2) responded with a 15-0 run over the next five minutes to take control. Brown made a pair of 3-pointers during the run and DaShaun Wood added five points. Cleveland State got no closer than 11 the rest of the way. Brown shot 8-for-14 and made four of his seven 3-point shots. The Raiders held the Vikings to 6-for-25 shooting on 3-pointers. Patrick Tatham and Joe Davis led Cleveland State with 12 points each and Victor Morris added 10. Wood scored 14 for Wright State and Drew Burleson added 13 points and nine rebounds.
